reviews.review_text:
Awesome place to have authentic Telugu food here. Wasn't expecting this in Goa. Happy to be here for the next time veg food options.
Prawns fry was lip smacking.
But they closed the counter bit early like 10:45 PM is the last order time so kindly make note of it.
Overall nice place to be with family n friends.

We were of 4 members from hyderabad and we got shocked to see the quantity of chicken served for rs350 rs450 which is way less than one can imagine. The gongura chicken pulav had oil overflowing. I understand gongura takes bit more oil than other leaves, but there are better ways to reduce oil. Spl Biryani was not that great for rs450 as per these reviews. There is no point of selling dishes at this price when there is no value added to them. Just because there are less andhra cousin options in goa doesn't mean it will never have. Please improve the quantity, lessen the price and oil. We wont come here again and will not recommend anyone. Makes me wonder if these reviews are real. We left utterly dissapointed and money wasted with half filled stomach. I suggest you all going to mana andhra ruchulu in calangute which is by far affordable and real.

Update: reply to owner -
The reply shows your audacity. I have paid for the food you served us and you expect not to give any feedback? I would have surely shared this feedback if you had asked us on spot about the food. Hence I am recording it here. Grow up and learn to take a feedback amd improve yourself instead of asking me not to come again. Moreover I have already mentioned i wont come already.

All my reviews are my personal genuine feelings for what I have enjoyed or disliked (unlike the fake ones here). If you cant handle such reviews, better unlist yourself from Google maps. It will help genuine people like us to avoid places like this. I guess its high time to see trend of your reviews/feedback rather than checking the trend of your customer's timeline.

I have updated 2 stars from 1 star just to spread some positivity.
The food was awesome. It was literally feeling like I was having my home food. Spice level is also less. Overall food and ambience is awesome.

**Restaurant Review: Trails Of Taste (TOT)¬Æ - Authentic Andhra Dining Experience in Goa**

Tucked away in the serene Corlim Industrial Estate, Trails Of Taste (TOT)¬Æ redefines Telugu culinary traditions within the vibrant spectrum of Goa‚Äôs diverse dining scene. With an impressive rating of 4.6 stars from a commendable 2,681 patrons, this restaurant has garnered attention not only for its flavorful offerings but also for its cultural authenticity. Key highlights from customer feedback point to specialty dishes such as *Gongura Chicken* and *Chicken Pulao*, alongside a divine *Prawns Fry*, resonating well with diners seeking genuine Andhra flavors.

**Ambiance & Design**

Upon entering Trails Of Taste, one is immediately welcomed by a warm and inviting ambiance that reflects the rich cultural heritage of Andhra Pradesh. The d√©cor features traditional elements, harmoniously intertwined with modern touches, creating a cozy yet vibrant environment. Soft, ambient lighting casts a gentle glow across rustic wooden tables, while framed photographs of Andhra heritage subtly adorn the walls. The atmosphere is lively, further enhanced by the sound of Telugu songs wafting through the air, evoking nostalgia for many diners. As seen in various customer-contributed images, each corner of the restaurant tells a story, making it an ideal spot for families and friends to come together.

**Menu & Culinary Experience**

The menu at Trails Of Taste is a celebration of Andhra cuisine, boasting an array of mouthwatering dishes that cater to diverse palates. The *Chicken Pulao* and *Gongura Chicken* are standout dishes that often receive rave reviews, with customers praising their bold flavors and authentic taste. However, some diners have noted inconsistencies regarding portion sizes and oil content in certain dishes, making it a mixed bag in terms of value for money.

Presentation wise, dishes are served with an eye for aesthetics, often accompanied by traditional condiments and garnishes that enhance the visual appeal of the meals. Although there is a limited selection for vegetarians, several patrons have appreciated the homemade quality of the food, with some asserting that it evokes the comforting flavors of home-cooked meals.

**Customer Experience & Service**

Customer service at Trails Of Taste boasts a friendly demeanor, with staff members going out of their way to make diners feel at home. However, there have been some concerns voiced regarding the restaurant's closing time, with a few guests wishing for a later last order time to accommodate their dining plans. Despite these minor hurdles, customers have expressed that the overall experience is pleasant, often choosing to return for the unrivaled flavors.

**Popularity & Reviews**

The buzz surrounding Trails Of Taste is palpable on social media, with many food enthusiasts sharing their experiences and visual impressions of the delectable dishes. Some critiques have pointed out room for improvement regarding portion sizes and prices; however, a majority of diners still echo sentiments of satisfaction regarding the taste and authenticity of the food. Such ratings not only reflect the culinary delights but also the restaurant‚Äôs dedication to promoting Andhra culture in a region where it is less prevalent.

**Utilizing Visual Content**

The restaurant‚Äôs aesthetic charm is amplified through customer-shared images, showcasing not only the thoughtful presentation of dishes but also the inviting atmosphere that characterizes Trails Of Taste. From mouthwatering shots of *Prawns Fry* to the beautifully arranged *Gongura Chicken*, each photo encapsulates the heart of the dining experience here. These visuals, which impressively detail the vibrant colors and textures of each dish, serve as an enticing invitation for potential guests who are eager to indulge in authentic Andhra cuisine.

In conclusion, Trails Of Taste (TOT)¬Æ stands out as a beacon of traditional Andhra cooking in Goa, melding authenticity with a welcoming atmosphere. Its unique approach to cherished recipes resonates well with patrons, making it a noteworthy destination for those looking to savor quality Telugu fare. While some aspects warrant attention, the restaurant's rich flavors and cultural resonance likely ensure a loyal following for years to come.
